rate_limits.name: babbage-002
rate_limits.tagline: Replacement for the GPT-3 ada and babbage base models
rate_limits.description: GPT base models can understand and generate natural language or code but are not trained with instruction following. These models are made to be replacements for our original GPT-3 base models and use the legacy Completions API. Most customers should use GPT-3.5 or GPT-4.

rate_limits.name: chatgpt-4o-latest
rate_limits.tagline: GPT-4o model used in ChatGPT
rate_limits.description:
ChatGPT-4o points to the GPT-4o snapshot currently used in ChatGPT. GPT-4o is our versatile, high-intelligence flagship model.
It accepts both text and image inputs, and produces text outputs.
It is the best model for most tasks, and is our most capable model outside of our o-series models.

rate_limits.name: codex-mini-latest
rate_limits.tagline: Fast reasoning model optimized for the Codex CLI
rate_limits.description:
codex-mini-latest is a fine-tuned version of o4-mini specifically
for use in Codex CLI. For direct use in the API, we recommend starting 
with gpt-4.1.

rate_limits.name: computer-use-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Specialized model for computer use tool
rate_limits.description:
The computer-use-preview model is a specialized model for the computer use 
tool. It is trained to understand and execute computer tasks.
See the [computer use guide](/docs/guides/tools-computer-use) for more
information. This model is only usable in the 
[Responses API](/docs/api-reference/responses).

rate_limits.name: dall-e-2
rate_limits.tagline: Our first image generation model
rate_limits.description: DALL·E is an AI system that creates realistic images and art from a natural language description. Older than DALL·E 3, DALL·E 2 offers more control in prompting and more requests at once.

rate_limits.name: dall-e-3
rate_limits.tagline: Previous generation image generation model
rate_limits.description: DALL·E is an AI system that creates realistic images and art from a natural language description. DALL·E 3 currently supports the ability, given a prompt, to create a new image with a specific size.

rate_limits.name: davinci-002
rate_limits.tagline: Replacement for the GPT-3 curie and davinci base models
rate_limits.description: GPT base models can understand and generate natural language or code but are not trained with instruction following. These models are made to be replacements for our original GPT-3 base models and use the legacy Completions API. Most customers should use GPT-3.5 or GPT-4.

rate_limits.name: gpt-3.5-turbo-16k-0613
rate_limits.tagline: Legacy GPT model for cheaper chat and non-chat tasks
rate_limits.description: GPT-3.5 Turbo models can understand and generate natural language or code and have been optimized for chat using the Chat Completions API but work well for non-chat tasks as well. As of July 2024, use gpt-4o-mini in place of GPT-3.5 Turbo, as it is cheaper, more capable, multimodal, and just as fast. GPT-3.5 Turbo is still available for use in the API.

rate_limits.name: gpt-3.5-turbo-instruct
rate_limits.tagline: An older model only compatible with the legacy Completions endpoint
rate_limits.description: Similar capabilities as GPT-3 era models. Compatible with legacy Completions endpoint and not Chat Completions.

rate_limits.name: gpt-3.5-turbo
rate_limits.tagline: Legacy GPT model for cheaper chat and non-chat tasks
rate_limits.description: GPT-3.5 Turbo models can understand and generate natural language or code and have been optimized for chat using the Chat Completions API but work well for non-chat tasks as well. As of July 2024, use gpt-4o-mini in place of GPT-3.5 Turbo, as it is cheaper, more capable, multimodal, and just as fast. GPT-3.5 Turbo is still available for use in the API.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4-turbo-preview
rate_limits.tagline: An older fast GPT model
rate_limits.description: This is a research preview of the GPT-4 Turbo model, an older high-intelligence GPT model.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4-turbo
rate_limits.tagline: An older high-intelligence GPT model
rate_limits.description: GPT-4 Turbo is the next generation of GPT-4, an older high-intelligence GPT model. It was designed to be a cheaper, better version of GPT-4. Today, we recommend using a newer model like GPT-4o.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4.1-mini
rate_limits.tagline: Balanced for intelligence, speed, and cost
rate_limits.description:
GPT-4.1 mini provides a balance between intelligence, speed, and cost that
makes it an attractive model for many use cases.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4.1-nano
rate_limits.tagline: Fastest, most cost-effective GPT-4.1 model
rate_limits.description: GPT-4.1 nano is the fastest, most cost-effective GPT-4.1 model.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4.1
rate_limits.tagline: Flagship GPT model for complex tasks
rate_limits.description:
GPT-4.1 is our flagship model for complex tasks. It is well suited for problem
solving across domains.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4.5-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Largest and most capable GPT model
rate_limits.description: This is a research preview of GPT-4.5, our largest and most capable GPT model yet. Its deep world knowledge and better understanding of user intent makes it good at creative tasks and agentic planning. GPT-4.5 excels at tasks that benefit from creative, open-ended thinking and conversation, such as writing, learning, or exploring new ideas.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4
rate_limits.tagline: An older high-intelligence GPT model
rate_limits.description: GPT-4 is an older version of a high-intelligence GPT model, usable in Chat Completions.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-audio-preview
rate_limits.tagline: GPT-4o models capable of audio inputs and outputs
rate_limits.description:
This is a preview release of the GPT-4o Audio models. These models accept 
audio inputs and outputs, and can be used in the Chat Completions REST API.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-mini-audio-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Smaller model capable of audio inputs and outputs
rate_limits.description: This is a preview release of the smaller GPT-4o Audio mini model. It's designed to input audio or create audio outputs via the REST API.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-mini-realtime-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Smaller realtime model for text and audio inputs and outputs
rate_limits.description: This is a preview release of the GPT-4o-mini Realtime model, capable of responding to audio and text inputs in realtime over WebRTC or a WebSocket interface.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-mini-search-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Fast, affordable small model for web search
rate_limits.description: GPT-4o mini Search Preview is a specialized model trained to understand and execute [web search](/docs/guides/tools-web-search?api-mode=chat) queries with the Chat Completions API. In addition to token fees, web search queries have a fee per tool call. Learn more in the [pricing](/docs/pricing) page.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-mini-transcribe
rate_limits.tagline: Speech-to-text model powered by GPT-4o mini
rate_limits.description:
GPT-4o mini Transcribe is a speech-to-text model that uses GPT-4o mini to transcribe audio.
It offers improvements to word error rate and better language recognition and accuracy compared to original Whisper models. Use it for more accurate transcripts.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-mini-tts
rate_limits.tagline: Text-to-speech model powered by GPT-4o mini
rate_limits.description: GPT-4o mini TTS is a text-to-speech model built on GPT-4o mini, a fast and powerful language model. Use it to convert text to natural sounding spoken text. The maximum number of input tokens is 2000.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-mini
rate_limits.tagline: Fast, affordable small model for focused tasks
rate_limits.description:
GPT-4o mini (“o” for “omni”) is a fast, affordable small model for focused tasks. 
It accepts both text and image inputs, and produces text outputs (including Structured Outputs). 
It is ideal for fine-tuning, and model outputs from a larger model like GPT-4o can be distilled to GPT-4o-mini to produce similar results at lower cost and latency.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-realtime-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Model capable of realtime text and audio inputs and outputs
rate_limits.description: This is a preview release of the GPT-4o Realtime model, capable of responding to audio and text inputs in realtime over WebRTC or a WebSocket interface.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-search-preview
rate_limits.tagline: GPT model for web search in Chat Completions
rate_limits.description: GPT-4o Search Preview is a specialized model trained to understand and execute [web search](/docs/guides/tools-web-search?api-mode=chat) queries with the Chat Completions API. In addition to token fees, web search queries have a fee per tool call. Learn more in the [pricing](/docs/pricing) page.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o-transcribe
rate_limits.tagline: Speech-to-text model powered by GPT-4o
rate_limits.description:
GPT-4o Transcribe is a speech-to-text model that uses GPT-4o to transcribe audio.
It offers improvements to word error rate and better language recognition and accuracy compared to original Whisper models. Use it for more accurate transcripts.

rate_limits.name: gpt-4o
rate_limits.tagline: Fast, intelligent, flexible GPT model
rate_limits.description:
GPT-4o (“o” for “omni”) is our versatile, high-intelligence flagship model.
It accepts both text and image inputs, and produces text outputs (including Structured Outputs).
It is the best model for most tasks, and is our most capable model outside of our o-series models.

rate_limits.name: gpt-image-1
rate_limits.tagline: State-of-the-art image generation model
rate_limits.description: GPT Image 1 is our new state-of-the-art image generation model. It is a natively multimodal language model that accepts both text and image inputs, and produces image outputs.

rate_limits.name: o1-mini
rate_limits.tagline: A small model alternative to o1
rate_limits.description: The o1 reasoning model is designed to solve hard problems across domains. o1-mini is a faster and more affordable reasoning model, but we recommend using the newer o3-mini model that features higher intelligence at the same latency and price as o1-mini.

rate_limits.name: o1-preview
rate_limits.tagline: Preview of our first o-series reasoning model
rate_limits.description: Research preview of the o1 series of models, trained with reinforcement learning to perform complex reasoning. o1 models think before they answer, producing a long internal chain of thought before responding to the user.

rate_limits.name: o1-pro
rate_limits.tagline: Version of o1 with more compute for better responses
rate_limits.description:
The o1 series of models are trained with reinforcement learning to think 
before they answer and perform complex reasoning. The o1-pro model uses more 
compute to think harder and provide consistently better answers.

o1-pro is available in the [Responses API only](/docs/api-reference/responses)
to enable support for multi-turn model interactions before responding to API
requests, and other advanced API features in the future.

rate_limits.name: o1
rate_limits.tagline: Previous full o-series reasoning model
rate_limits.description: The o1 series of models are trained with reinforcement learning to perform complex reasoning. o1 models think before they answer, producing a long internal chain of thought before responding to the user.

rate_limits.name: o3-deep-research
rate_limits.tagline: Our most powerful deep research model
rate_limits.description:
o3-deep-research is our most advanced model for deep research, 
designed to tackle complex, multi-step research tasks. It can 
search and synthesize information from across the internet as 
well as from your own data—brought in through MCP connectors.

Learn more about getting started with this model in our
[deep research](/docs/guides/deep-research) guide.

rate_limits.name: o3-mini
rate_limits.tagline: A small model alternative to o3
rate_limits.description: o3-mini is our newest small reasoning model, providing high intelligence at the same cost and latency targets of o1-mini. o3-mini supports key developer features, like Structured Outputs, function calling, and Batch API.

rate_limits.name: o3-pro
rate_limits.tagline: Version of o3 with more compute for better responses
rate_limits.description:
The o-series of models are trained with reinforcement learning to think 
before they answer and perform complex reasoning. The o3-pro model uses more 
compute to think harder and provide consistently better answers.

o3-pro is available in the [Responses API only](/docs/api-reference/responses)
to enable support for multi-turn model interactions before responding to API 
requests, and other advanced API features in the future. Since o3-pro is designed 
to tackle tough problems, some requests may take several minutes to finish. 
To avoid timeouts, try using [background mode](/docs/guides/background).

rate_limits.name: o3
rate_limits.tagline: Our most powerful reasoning model
rate_limits.description:
o3 is a well-rounded and powerful model across domains. It sets a new standard for math, science, coding, and visual reasoning tasks. It also excels at technical writing and instruction-following. Use it to think through multi-step problems that involve analysis across text, code, and images. 

Learn more about how to use our reasoning models in our [reasoning](/docs/guides/reasoning?api-mode=responses) guide.

rate_limits.name: o4-mini-deep-research
rate_limits.tagline: Faster, more affordable deep research model
rate_limits.description:
o4-mini-deep-research is our faster, more affordable deep 
research model—ideal for tackling complex, multi-step research 
tasks. It can search and synthesize information from across the 
internet as well as from your own data, brought in through 
MCP connectors.

Learn more about how to use this model in our
[deep research](/docs/guides/deep-research) guide.

rate_limits.name: o4-mini
rate_limits.tagline: Faster, more affordable reasoning model
rate_limits.description:
o4-mini is our latest small o-series model. It's optimized for fast, effective reasoning with exceptionally efficient performance in coding and visual tasks. 

Learn more about how to use our reasoning models in our [reasoning](/docs/guides/reasoning?api-mode=responses) guide.

rate_limits.name: omni-moderation-latest
rate_limits.tagline: Identify potentially harmful content in text and images
rate_limits.description:
Moderation models are free models designed to detect harmful content.
This model is our most capable moderation model, accepting images as input as well.

rate_limits.name: text-embedding-3-large
rate_limits.tagline: Most capable embedding model
rate_limits.description:
text-embedding-3-large is our most capable embedding model for both english and non-english tasks.
Embeddings are a numerical representation of text that can be used to measure the relatedness between two pieces of text.
Embeddings are useful for search, clustering, recommendations, anomaly detection, and classification tasks.

rate_limits.name: text-embedding-3-small
rate_limits.tagline: Small embedding model
rate_limits.description:
text-embedding-3-small is our improved, more performant version of our ada embedding model.
Embeddings are a numerical representation of text that can be used to measure the relatedness between two pieces of text.
Embeddings are useful for search, clustering, recommendations, anomaly detection, and classification tasks.

rate_limits.name: text-embedding-ada-002
rate_limits.tagline: Older embedding model
rate_limits.description:
text-embedding-ada-002 is our improved, more performant version of our ada embedding model.
Embeddings are a numerical representation of text that can be used to measure the relatedness between two pieces of text.
Embeddings are useful for search, clustering, recommendations, anomaly detection, and classification tasks.

rate_limits.name: tts-1-hd
rate_limits.tagline: Text-to-speech model optimized for quality
rate_limits.description: TTS is a model that converts text to natural sounding spoken text. The tts-1-hd model is optimized for high quality text-to-speech use cases. Use it with the Speech endpoint in the Audio API.

rate_limits.name: tts-1
rate_limits.tagline: Text-to-speech model optimized for speed
rate_limits.description: TTS is a model that converts text to natural sounding spoken text. The tts-1 model is optimized for realtime text-to-speech use cases. Use it with the Speech endpoint in the Audio API.

rate_limits.name: whisper-1
rate_limits.tagline: General-purpose speech recognition model
rate_limits.description: Whisper is a general-purpose speech recognition model, trained on a large dataset of diverse audio. You can also use it as a multitask model to perform multilingual speech recognition as well as speech translation and language identification.
